Former President Soeharto, his family, cronies, and senior officials enjoyed privileges beyond the Soeharto family.
Companies and foundations under Soeharto's control amassed vast wealth.
Soedjono evasively defended Soeharto's right to privacy.
Estimates suggest Soeharto's fortune exceeded $40 billion, while his family's assets reached $20 billion.
Amid calls for reform, investigations into Soeharto's wealth intensified.
Allegations of illegal wealth accumulation and overseas stashing prompted public outrage.
Demonstrations demanding justice for corruption, collusion, and nepotism marked a turning point in Indonesia's political landscape.
